description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nursing &amp; Rehabilitation Assistant, Band 2&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;£18,005 per annum + HCAS £3,7284 per annum&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Would you like to work for an organisation that is progressive, innovative and provides quality care for families in Bromley? To find out what its like to work for Bromley Healthcare please view our videos on YouTube, search for Bromley healthcare and you will get a flavour of Bromley healthcare.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are currently looking for Nursing &amp; Rehab Assistants to join our dynamic, friendly team who are patient focused and thrive on providing quality care.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bromley Healthcare is one of the first Social Enterprise’s working successfully with the NHS and has been established since 2011. The benefits of this approach are high productivity, greater innovation, better care and greater job satisfaction for the professionals and support staff working in the organisation. This results in driving improvement in services for our families.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are looking for enthusiastic and compassionate Nursing Rehabilitation Assistants to join the team at our 28 bedded Rehabilitation Unit based within Foxbury Ward at Queen Mary&#39;s Hospital&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our aim is for patients to become as independent as possible in a person centred, caring environment. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are a multi disciplinary team working together to ensure patients meet their rehabilitation potential prior to going home.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You would be working alongside Nurses, Drs, Physiotherapists, Occupational therapists, Social Services and Administrative staff in a Nurse led clinical environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A healthcare/caring background &amp; experience is preferred.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The post holder is expected to work within the requirements of the 6 C’s – Care, Compassion, Competence, Communication, Courage and Commitment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please see attached job description and person specification for more information&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Val Ritchie Matron or Maria Moody Junior Sister&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;0300 003 1216&lt;/p&gt;
